parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake pads can cause vibration, noise, and reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibration when braking
noise when braking
premature wear of brake pads
frequent replacement of brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Shoes Grabbing/Making Noise in Moist Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake shoes grabbing or making noise in moist conditions can cause reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake shoes grabbing or making noise when braking in moist conditions
reduced braking performance in wet weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear ABS Brake Proportioning Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rear ABS brake proportioning valve can cause uneven braking, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear ABS brakes only engaging at 90-100% on the front wheels
frequent replacement of rotors and shoes
uneven braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation at high speeds can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation occurs without prior tire deflation
resulting in debris that can cause minor damage to the vehicle's paint and trim.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt latching mechanism can lead to the seat belt unbuckling unexpectedly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt latch unlocks while driving
the seat belt buckle can be unlocked when the brakes are applied
the seat belt buckle does not stay locked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt buckle extension can prevent the seat belt from being properly secured, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger seat belt buckle will not extend from its housing
making it difficult or impossible to properly secure the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank detaching from the vehicle while driving can cause a fuel leak, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially resulting in a vehicle crash or explosion.
symptoms: The fuel tank falls off the vehicle
fuel leaks onto the road
the vehicle catches fire
the driver hears a loud noise or feels a sudden jolt
the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system after a minor collision can cause a fire to break out, potentially resulting in a vehicle crash or explosion.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
flames are visible from the rear of the vehicle
the driver smells fuel or smoke
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
the driver hears a hissing or popping sound.
